          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>Unknown number of fol.; Writing surface: paper; Shelfmark: Y. 4667; Qurʾānic Text: beginning – 93:11; 15 lines per page; Dimensions: 215 x 270mm; Script style: nasḫ.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p><ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UEN2FUP7" sameAs="UEN2FUP7" type="zotero">Karatay (1962) </ref>describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 27: "82 Y. 4667. Aynı. Esmer kâğıt. 270mm boy ve 215mm Arap neshiyle 180mm eninde … yaprak. Sahifede Arap neshiyle 180mm uzunl.[uğunda] 15 satır. Tahminen VI. (XII) asırda kopya edilmiştir. Baştan iki yaprağı sonradan yazılmıştır. Miklep ve oyma şemseli ünnabî deri cilt. Sonu Żuḥa [Duha] (93) suresine kadardır."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "82 Y. 4667. Same. Brown paper. … leaves of 270 mm height and 215 mm width. The text area written in naskh script [contains] 15 lines measuring 180 mm. Probably copied during the 6th (12th) century. The first two leafs were added later. Leather unnabī binding with flap (miklep) and carved mandorla (şemse). It is until the Q 93 (Sūra al-Ḍuḥā).”</p>
            </summary>
